Dymon Asia Currency Value Fund
The Dymon Asia Currency Value Fund is designed to generate upside volatility and aims to return 15%
to 30% net per annum on a notional basis. Portfolio core holdings are mostly medium term FX
options with 6 to 18 months horizon. We intend to hold these options to maturity, while using FX
spot and forward to keep an efficient portfolio. Portfolio is structured in a way to cap the maximum
amount the Fund can lose premiums which have been paid, thereby truncating tail-risk. 








































