Dymon Asia Currency Value Fund Form D
The Singapore-based Dymon Asia Currency Value Fund had published Form D because of $173.61 million offering. The date of first sale was 2012-01-03. The raised $173.61 million. The offering is still open. The total offering amount amount was $173.61 million. The offering form was filed on 2015-10-05. Dymon Asia Currency Value Fund’s clarification was: unspecified. 
 Dymon Asia Currency Value Fund is based in Singapore. The firm’s business is Pooled Investment Fund. The SEC form was submitted by Jason Eng General Counsel. The company was incorporated in 2011. The filler’s address is: Dymon Asia Capital Ltd, 190 Elgin Avenue, George Town, Grand Cayman, E9, Cayman Islands, Ky1-9005. Dymon Asia Capital Ltd is the related person in the form and it has address: 190 Elgin Avenue, George Town, Grand Cayman, E9, Cayman Islands, Ky1-9005. Link to Dymon Asia Currency Value Fund Filing: 000153974315000001.
Analysis of Dymon Asia Currency Value Fund Offering
On average, firms in the Pooled Investment Fund sector, sell 37.80% investment fund interests. Dymon Asia Currency Value Fund sold 100.00% of the offering. The average investment size is $24.76 million for companies in the Pooled Investment Fund industry sector. The minimum investment for Dymon Asia Currency Value Fund ‘s offering was $1000000.

